# sample website for API: https://restful-api.dev/

API (Application Programming Interface):

HTTP Methods:
1. GET
2. POST
3. PUT
4. PATCH
5. DELETE

Response Code:

100-199: Information response code
200-299 : Success response
300-399 : Re-directional response
400-499 : Client error response
500-599 : Server Error Response

# https://restfulapi.net/http-status-codes/

# API based on Architecture:

Rest (Representational State Transfer) API: This type API are stateless API, this faster in term of speed

SOAP (Simple Object Access Protocol) API:This is called xml based messaging protocol where it maintain
the state of API.

XML Structure:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<api_request_root_element>
    <authentication>
        <username>your_username</username>
        <api_key>your_api_key</api_key>
    </authentication>
    <request_details>
        <method_name>createItem</method_name>
        <parameters>
            <item>
                <field_id>123</field_id>
                <value>New Item Name</value>
            </item>
            <!-- More parameters can be nested here -->
        </parameters>
    </request_details>
</api_request_root_element>